{"title_page": "Resident Evil 3 (2020 video game)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Short description|2020 survival horror video game remake}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Resident Evil 3\n| image = Resident Evil 3.jpg\n| developer = [[Capcom]]{{efn|With assistance from K2 Inc, M-Two, and Redworks. The game's multiplayer mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', was co-developed with NeoBards Entertainment<ref>https://neobards.com/neobards-entertainment-in-partnership-with-capcom-co-ltd-is-very-proud-to-present-the-upcoming-release-of-their-newest-masterpiece-project-resistance/</ref>.}}\n| publisher = Capcom\n| director = {{Unbulleted list|Kiyohiko Sakata|Yasuhiro Seto|Yasuhiro Anpo|Yukio Ando}}\n| producer = Masachika Kawata\n| designer = {{Unbulleted list|Masanori Komine|Takashi Ishihara}}\n| programmer = Go Azawa\n| artist = {{Unbulleted list|Cho Yonghee|Yuka Chi}}\n| composer = {{Unbulleted list|Kota Suzuki|Azusa Kato}}\n| series = ''[[Resident Evil]]''\n| engine = <!--Wikidata-->\n| released = April 3, 2020\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]||[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]}}\n| genre = [[Survival horror]]\n| modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Resident Evil 3'''''{{efn|{{Nihongo|Known in Japan as '''''Biohazard RE:3'''''|\u30d0\u30a4\u30aa\u30cf\u30b6\u30fc\u30c9 RE:3|Baiohaz\u0101do \u0100ru \u012a Sur\u012b|lead=yes}} and referred to as ''Resident Evil 3 Remake'' or ''RE3 Remake'' to differentiate from the original game.}} is a [[survival horror]] game developed and published by [[Capcom]]. It is a [[video game remake|remake]] of ''[[Resident Evil 3: Nemesis]]'' (1999) and follows [[Jill Valentine]] and [[Carlos Oliveira (Resident Evil)|Carlos Oliveira]] as they attempt to survive a [[zombie apocalypse]] while hunted by the intelligent [[bioweapon]] [[Nemesis (Resident Evil)|Nemesis]]. It was released on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on April 3, 2020. It also released alongside an [[online multiplayer]] game, ''[[Resident Evil: Resistance]]''.\n\nThe game received generally favorable reviews, with praise for its graphics, presentation, [[LGBT]] themes, female protagonist and gameplay. It was criticized for its short length, pacing, and absence of elements from the original game. The game shipped over two million copies within a month.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Resident Evil 3'' is a remake of ''[[Resident Evil 3: Nemesis]]'', a [[survival horror]] video game released for the [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] in 1999, followed by releases for Microsoft Windows and [[Dreamcast|Sega Dreamcast]] in 2000, and [[GameCube|Nintendo GameCube]] in 2003. Unlike the original, which uses [[tank controls]] and fixed camera angles, the remake features [[third-person shooter]] gameplay similar to the [[Resident Evil 2 (2019 video game)|2019 ''Resident Evil 2'' remake]]. {{anchor|Resident Evil: Resistance}}It includes an [[online multiplayer]] mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', which puts a team of four players against a \"mastermind\" who can create traps, enemies, and other hazards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wakeling |first1=Richard |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Official Release Date On Consoles And PC Announced; RE Resistance Multiplayer Included |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-official-release-date-on-co/1100-6472063/ |website=GameSpot |accessdate=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212111645/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-official-release-date-on-co/1100-6472063/ |archive-date=December 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The beginning of ''Resident Evil 3'' however, has players briefly controlling Jill in a [[first person perspective]], in a nightmare, and then in her apartment, engaging with the environment around her much like the characters the players assume the role of in ''[[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]''.<ref>https://www.gamerevolution.com/guides/641723-resident-evil-3-remake-first-person-mode-pc-ps4-xbox-one</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n[[Raccoon City]] is thrown into chaos by a [[zombie apocalypse]] caused by an outbreak of the [[T-Virus]]. On September 28, 1998, former Special Tactics And Rescue Service (S.T.A.R.S.) member [[Jill Valentine]] is attacked in her apartment by an intelligent [[Biological agent|bioweapon]] known as [[Nemesis (Resident Evil)|Nemesis-T Type]], who attempts to kill her and all remaining members of S.T.A.R.S.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shapiro |first1=Micah |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake: Clues For An Expanded Story |url=https://gamerant.com/resident-evil-3-remake-story-clues/ |website=Game Rant |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231255/https://gamerant.com/resident-evil-3-remake-story-clues/ |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Upon escaping her building, she meets up with fellow S.T.A.R.S. officer [[Brad Vickers]], but Brad is bitten by a zombie and tells Jill to save herself. After another encounter with Nemesis, she is saved by Umbrella Biohazard Countermeasure Service (U.B.C.S.) mercenary [[Carlos Oliveira (Resident Evil)|Carlos Oliveira]]. Carlos and his group of surviving U.B.C.S. mercenaries - [[Mikhail Victor]], Tyrell Patrick, and [[Nicholai Ginovaef]] - have set up subway trains which they plan to use to evacuate surviving civilians from the city. \n\nAfter surviving several encounters with Nemesis, Jill manages to reactivate power to the subway, while Carlos and Tyrell remain in the city to search for Dr. Nathaniel Bard, an Umbrella scientist who might know how to make a vaccine for the T-virus and save the city. As Jill, Nicholai, and Mikhail depart in the train, Mikhail expresses his suspicions towards Nicholai on how their platoon was ambushed by zombies. Nemesis suddenly attacks the train and kills the civilians; Nicholai locks the other two out, forcing them to defend themselves. Nemesis grabs Mikhail, who sacrifices himself by detonating an explosive, causing the train to derail. Jill escapes as seemingly the only survivor of the crash.\n\nCarlos and Tyrell travel to the city's police department, where they plan to find Bard in the S.T.A.R.S. office. The two witness R.P.D. Lieutenant Marvin Branagh be bitten by a zombified Brad, who is killed by Carlos shortly afterwards. The two enter the S.T.A.R.S. office and communicate via video with Bard, who informs them that he is at a hospital. Meanwhile, as Tyrell traces Bard\u2019s location, Jill escapes the wreckage of the derailed train only to be again pursued by Nemesis who is now heavily mutated. Jill radios Carlos and engages the monster, managing to escape it, but only after it infects her with the T-virus. Jill falls unconscious and Carlos finds her roughly half a day later, taking her to Spencer Memorial Hospital - the location of Bard. Carlos fights his way through the infested hospital only to find that Bard has been murdered. He views a video from Bard confessing that the T-virus was engineered by Umbrella, and despite Umbrella hiring him to develop the vaccine, Umbrella's board now wants to destroy it and eliminate all traces of the virus' existence. Carlos retrieves the vaccine and administers it to Jill. Tyrell arrives at the hospital and they realize that the U.S. government plans to destroy Raccoon City in a missile strike to eradicate the T-Virus infestation. Carlos travels to the NEST 2 lab underneath the hospital to find more vaccines, while Tyrell tries to contact whoever he can to try and stop the missile strike.\n\nJill awakens on the day of the missile strike, October 1, and pursues Carlos to NEST 2. She encounters Nicholai, who is revealed to be a supervisor hired by an unknown contractor to sabotage Umbrella's efforts to hide their involvement and to observe and collect data from attacks of several bioweapons, including Nemesis. Nemesis kills Tyrell and continues to pursue Jill throughout the lab. Jill manages to synthesize a vaccine, but an encounter with Nemesis causes Nicholai to retrieve it for himself as he leaves her to fight the monster. Jill attempts to destroy Nemesis in a vat of solution designed to dispose of any biological waste only for Nemesis to further mutate into a giant mass of flesh with tentacles. Jill then uses a prototype [[railgun]] to finally eliminate Nemesis for good. At the hospital's roof deck, Nicholai disarms Jill and destroys the vaccine, acknowledging that he doesn't care for the city's fate as long as he gets paid for sabotaging Umbrella. Carlos intervenes and restrains Nicholai for Jill to shoot.{{efn|If missed or not shot, Nicholai kills Jill and Carlos.<ref name=\"IGNdetails\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/21-brilliant-details-in-resident-evil-3|title=21 Brilliant Little Details in Resident Evil 3|website=IGN|date=3 April 2020|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>}} When interrogated on who he works for, he says that he will tell her and pay her anything if he survives. Disgusted by his greed, Jill retrieves the destroyed vaccine case and escapes the city with Carlos via helicopter, leaving Nicholai for dead. The city is destroyed by the missile strike, and Jill promises to take down Umbrella.\n\n==Development==\n''Resident Evil 3'' was under development for approximately three years prior to its announcement in 2019.<ref>{{cite web| last1=Palumbo |first1=Alessio |title='Resident Evil 3' Has Far More Raccoon City Exploration Dodge Makes It Feel More Like an Action Game |url=https://wccftech.com/resident-evil-3-has-far-more-raccoon-city-exploration-dodge-makes-it-feel-more-like-an-action-game/ |website=wccftech |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307094447/https://wccftech.com/resident-evil-3-has-far-more-raccoon-city-exploration-dodge-makes-it-feel-more-like-an-action-game/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Possible remake\">{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/capcom-says-a-resident-evil-3-remake-is-possible-i-say-bring-it-on--541068.phtml |title=Capcom says a Resident Evil 3 remake is possible, I say 'bring it on' |website=[[Destructoid]] |last=Carter |first=Chris |date=February 2, 2019 |accessdate=February 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203082435/https://www.destructoid.com/capcom-says-a-resident-evil-3-remake-is-possible-i-say-bring-it-on--541068.phtml |archivedate=February 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Fabiano speaks with GamingBolt\">{{cite web| last1=Parijat |first1= Shubhankar |title=Resident Evil 3 Interview \u2013 Return to Raccoon City | url=https://gamingbolt.com/resident-evil-3-interview-return-to-raccoon-city |website=gamingbolt |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324211016/https://gamingbolt.com/resident-evil-3-interview-return-to-raccoon-city |archive-date=March 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Development was handled by [[Capcom]] with assistance from its subsidiary K2 Inc, and from external companies Redworks and M-Two, the latter being founded by former [[PlatinumGames]] CEO Tatsuya Minami.<ref name=\"Director\">{{cite web|last1=Robinson |first1=Andy |title=Platinum veteran revealed as Resident Evil 3 director |url=https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/platinum-veteran-revealed-as-resident-evil-3-director/ |website=videogameschronicle |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310004438/https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/platinum-veteran-revealed-as-resident-evil-3-director/ |archive-date=March 10, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://k2-games.com/|title=K2 Inc Official Page|accessdate=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324210022/http://k2-games.com/|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Minami's M-Two\">{{cite web|last1=Robinson |first1=Andy |title=Confirmed Former Platinum CEO is behind new Capcom-backed studio |url=https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/confirmed-former-platinum-ceo-is-behind-new-capcom-backed-studio/ |website=videogameschronicle |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330232332/https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/confirmed-former-platinum-ceo-is-behind-new-capcom-backed-studio/ |archive-date=March 31, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The game was created using the RE Engine that was used in ''[[Resident Evil 7]]'', ''[[Devil May Cry 5]]'' and the ''Resident Evil 2'' remake.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Holt |first1=Kris |title='Resident Evil 3' remake hits PS4, Xbox One and PC on April 3rd |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-release-date/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210213744/https://www.engadget.com/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-release-date/ |archive-date=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The multiplayer mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', was developed externally by NeoBards Entertainment and was previously announced as a separate game, ''Project Resistance''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/350590/Capcom_Unveils_Project_Resistance_a_New_Experience_Set_in_the_Resident_Evil_Universe.php|title=Capcom Unveils Project Resistance; a New Experience Set in the Resident Evil Universe|website=Gamasutra|accessdate=12 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231407/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/350590/Capcom_Unveils_Project_Resistance_a_New_Experience_Set_in_the_Resident_Evil_Universe.php|archive-date=December 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProducers Masachika Kawata and Peter Fabiano said the team tried to honor the more action-oriented approach of the original game.<ref name=\"DevMsg\">{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Alistair |title=The Resident Evil 3 Remake is Real, and it Comes with Project Resistance |url=https://www.kotaku.co.uk/2019/12/10/the-resident-evil-3-remake-is-real-and-it-comes-with-project-resistance |website=Kotaku |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211214352/https://www.kotaku.co.uk/2019/12/10/the-resident-evil-3-remake-is-real-and-it-comes-with-project-resistance |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> They altered character designs accordingly, with Jill wearing more practical apparel and Carlos Oliveira being \"more rough around the edges\".<ref name=\"DevMsg\"/> Nemesis, one of the central aspects of the game, was redesigned and given new ways to track down players compared to the Tyrant from ''Resident Evil 2''.<ref name=\"DevMsg\"/> In terms of its visual design, Fabiano mentioned that art director Yonghee Cho wanted to make Nemesis feel like he could fit in the reimagined and photorealistic Raccoon City and should feel like a prototype model, while adding that the development team wanted to give players the feeling that they were constantly being pursued by a relentless and agile bioweapon by striking a balance between having players feel anxious and also giving them periods of respite.<ref name=\"Fabiano speaks with GamingBolt\"/>\n\n==Release==\n''Resident Evil 3'' was announced during an online PlayStation presentation in December 2019, and was released on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\"Remake confirmed\">{{cite web |first=Chris|last=Priestman|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-confirmed-with-release-date |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Confirmed With Release Date |website=[[IGN]] |date=December 10, 2019 |accessdate=December 10, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210215425/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-confirmed-with-release-date |archivedate=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> A collector's edition was made available for the console versions and features a Jill Valentine figure, hardcover art book, Raccoon City map poster, and two-disc soundtrack.<ref name=\"Collectors edition\">{{cite web |first=Jenae |last=Sitzes |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-pre-order-guide-collectors-/1100-6472065/ |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Pre-Order Guide: Collector's Edition, Release Date, Pre-Order Bonus |website=[[GameSpot]] |date=December 11, 2019 |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211214238/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-pre-order-guide-collectors-/1100-6472065/ |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Romano |first1=Sal |title=Resident Evil 3 remake Collector\u2019s Edition announced for Europe |url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/resident-evil-3-remake-collectors-edition-announced-for-europe |website=Gematsu |accessdate=January 22, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125100943/https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/resident-evil-3-remake-collectors-edition-announced-for-europe |archive-date=January 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> A demo of the game was released on March 19, 2020, with a ''Resident Evil: Resistance'' beta released on March 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/resident-evil-3-demo-to-be-released-on-march-19-resident-evil-resistance-arriving-on-march-27|title=Resident Evil 3 Demo to be Released on March 19, Resident Evil Resistance Open Beta Arriving on March 27|first=Adam|last=Bankhurst|website=[[IGN]]|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (PC) 78/100<ref name=\"MCPC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/resident-evil-3 |title=Resident Evil 3 for PC Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref><br/>(PS4) 80/100<ref name=\"MCPS4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/resident-evil-3|title=Resident Evil 3 for PlayStation 4 Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><br/>(XONE) 84/100<ref name=\"MCXONE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/resident-evil-3|title=Resident Evil 3 for Xbox One Reviews|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| Destruct = 8/10<ref name=\"Destructoid\">{{cite web|last=Carter|first=Chris|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-resident-evil-3-2020--584528.phtml|title=Review: Resident Evil 3 (2020)|website=[[Destructoid]]|publisher=[[Enthusiast Gaming]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| EZA = 8.5/10<ref name=\"EZA\">{{cite web|last=Huber|first=Michael|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://easyallies.com/#!/review/resident-evil-3-2020|title=Review: Resident Evil 3 (2020)|website=[[Easy Allies]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| EGM = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"EGM\">{{cite web|last=L Patterson|first=Mollie|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://egmnow.com/resident-evil-3-review/|title=Resident Evil 3 review|website=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]]|publisher=EGM Media, LLC|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| Fam = 36/40<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=April 8, 2020 |url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/04/famitsu-review-scores-issue-1636\u00a0|title=Famitsu Review Scores: Issue 1636 |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| GI = 9/10<ref name=\"GI\">{{cite web|last=Reeves|first=Ben|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.gameinformer.com/review/resident-evil-3/resident-evil-3-review-a-relentless-terror|title=Resident Evil 3 Review \u2013 A Relentless Terror|website=[[Game Informer]]|publisher=[[GameStop]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| GameRev = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Faulkner|first=Jason|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.gamerevolution.com/review/641246-resident-evil-3-remake-review|title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Review|website=[[Game Revolution]]|publisher=[[CraveOnline]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 6/10<ref>{{cite web|last=Fillari|first=Alessandro|date=April 6, 2020|url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/resident-evil-3-remake-review-farewell-raccoon-cit/1900-6417441/|title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Review - Farewell, Raccoon City|website=[[GameSpot]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| GRadar = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Hurley|first=Leon|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/resident-evil-3-remake-review/|title=RESIDENT EVIL 3 REVIEW: \u201cA TENSE, JUMPY RETELLING OF THE PS1 CLASSIC IN A MODERN GAMING LANGUAGE\u201d|website=[[GamesRadar+]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| HCG = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Wells|first=Cory|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://hardcoregamer.com/2020/03/30/review-resident-evil-3/370371/|title=Review: Resident Evil 3|website=Hardcore Gamer|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| IGN = 9/10<ref name=\"IGN\">{{cite web|last=O'Brien|first=Lucy|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/resident-evil-3-single-player-review-2|title=Resident Evil 3 Single-Player Review|website=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| JXV = 15/20<ref name=\"JXV\">{{cite web|last=de Carnbee|first=L'avis|date=March 30, 2020|url=http://www.jeuxvideo.com/test/1201834/resident-evil-3-un-adieu-explosif-pour-raccoon-city-malgre-une-relecture-inegale.htm|title=Resident Evil 3 : Un adieu explosif pour Raccoon City malgr\u00e9 une relecture in\u00e9gale|website=[[Jeuxvideo.com]]|publisher=Webedia|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| PCGUS = 58/100<ref name=\"PC Gamer\">{{cite web|last=Kelly|first=Andy|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/resident-evil-3-remake-review/|title=RESIDENT EVIL 3 REMAKE REVIEW|website=[[PC Gamer]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| PCGN = 7/10<ref name=\"PC GamesN\">{{cite web|last=Forward|first=Jordan|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/resident-evil-3/review|title=Resident Evil 3 review \u2013 missing in action|website=[[PCGamesN]]|publisher=[[Computec Media AG]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| USG = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"USgamer\">{{cite web|last=McCarthy|first=Caty|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/resident-evil-3-review|title=Resident Evil 3 Review: Earning the Big \"3\"|website=[[USgamer]]|publisher=[[Gamer Network]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| VG247 = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"VG247\">{{cite web|last=McKeand|first=Kirk|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.vg247.com/2020/03/30/resident-evil-3-remake-review/|title=Resident Evil 3 Remake review \u2013 a step backwards|website=[[VG247]]|publisher=videogaming247 Ltd|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| VG = 8/10<ref name=\"VG\">{{cite web|last=Wise|first=Josh|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://www.videogamer.com/reviews/resident-evil-3-review|title=Resident Evil 3 review|website=VideoGamer.com|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n''Resident Evil 3'' received \"generally favorable\" reviews, according to [[review aggregator]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPC\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4\"/><ref name=\"MCXONE\"/> It was praised for its graphics, sound, gameplay, and fast-paced horror. ''[[Kotaku]]'' gave the game a positive review, calling it \"an intense and confidently executed ''Resident Evil'' experience.\"<ref>https://kotaku.com/resident-evil-3-the-kotaku-review-1842559850</ref> IGN gave it 9/10 and said it was as strong as the ''Resident Evil 2'' remake.<ref name=\"IGN\"/>\n\n''[[GameSpot]]'' says that the game starts well but could not sustain it.<ref>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-review-round-up-whats-the-verdict/1100-6475388/</ref> ''[[PC Gamer]]'' gave the game a 58/100, saying: \"It's ultimately an extremely shallow game, with lavish production values failing to mask just how rushed and unambitious it feels.\"<ref name=\"PC Gamer\"/> ''[[Eurogamer]]'' also criticized the short length, saying \"all this - the pacing, the progression, the action and Nemesis' design, contributes to the feeling the ''Resident Evil 3'' remake is over too soon\".<ref>https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2020-03-30-resident-evil-3-remake-review-at-times-brilliant-but-not-a-patch-on-its-predecessor</ref> ''[[The Verge]]'' gave the game a positive review but noted the short length, saying that it was fun while it lasted.<ref>https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/30/21199382/resident-evil-3-remake-review-ps4-xbox-pc-2-capcom</ref>\n\nThe PlayStation 4 version sold 189,490 copies in its first week on sale in Japan, making it the second-bestselling retail game of the week there.<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=April 8, 2020 |url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/04/famitsu-sales-3-30-20-4-5-20\u00a0|title=Famitsu Sales: 3/30/20 \u2013 4/5/20 |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> After the first five days of release, the game has shipped over 2 million copies, with digital sales accounting for around half of this figure.<ref name=\"Shipped\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2020-04-13-resident-evil-3-remake-ships-2-million-in-five-days|title=Resident Evil 3 remake ships 2 million in five days|website=GamesIndustry.biz|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate= April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Footnotes==\n===Notes===\n{{Notelist}}\n===References===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.residentevil.com/re3}}\n{{Resident Evil series}}\n\n[[Category:2020 video games]]\n[[Category:Bioterrorism in fiction]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Resident Evil games]]\n[[Category:Video game remakes]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]\n[[Category:Video games set in 1998]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Short description|2020 survival horror video game remake}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Resident Evil 3\n| image = Resident Evil 3.jpg\n| developer = [[Capcom]]{{efn|With assistance from K2 Inc, M-Two, and Redworks. The game's multiplayer mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', was co-developed with NeoBards Entertainment<ref>https://neobards.com/neobards-entertainment-in-partnership-with-capcom-co-ltd-is-very-proud-to-present-the-upcoming-release-of-their-newest-masterpiece-project-resistance/</ref>.}}\n| publisher = Capcom\n| director = {{Unbulleted list|Kiyohiko Sakata|Yasuhiro Seto|Yasuhiro Anpo|Yukio Ando}}\n| producer = Masachika Kawata\n| designer = {{Unbulleted list|Masanori Komine|Takashi Ishihara}}\n| programmer = Go Azawa\n| artist = {{Unbulleted list|Cho Yonghee|Yuka Chi}}\n| composer = {{Unbulleted list|Kota Suzuki|Azusa Kato}}\n| series = ''[[Resident Evil]]''\n| engine = <!--Wikidata-->\n| released = April 3, 2020\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]||[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]}}\n| genre = [[Survival horror]]\n| modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Resident Evil 3'''''{{efn|{{Nihongo|Known in Japan as '''''Biohazard RE:3'''''|\u30d0\u30a4\u30aa\u30cf\u30b6\u30fc\u30c9 RE:3|Baiohaz\u0101do \u0100ru \u012a Sur\u012b|lead=yes}} and referred to as ''Resident Evil 3 Remake'' or ''RE3 Remake'' to differentiate from the original game.}} is a [[survival horror]] game developed and published by [[Capcom]]. It is a [[video game remake|remake]] of ''[[Resident Evil 3: Nemesis]]'' (1999) and follows [[Jill Valentine]] and [[Carlos Oliveira (Resident Evil)|Carlos Oliveira]] as they attempt to survive a [[zombie apocalypse]] while hunted by the intelligent [[bioweapon]] [[Nemesis (Resident Evil)|Nemesis]]. It was released on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on April 3, 2020. It also released alongside an [[online multiplayer]] game, ''[[Resident Evil: Resistance]]''.\n\nThe game received generally favorable reviews, with praise for its graphics, presentation, and gameplay. It was criticized for its short length, pacing, and absence of elements from the original game. The game shipped over two million copies within a month.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Resident Evil 3'' is a remake of ''[[Resident Evil 3: Nemesis]]'', a [[survival horror]] video game released for the [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] in 1999, followed by releases for Microsoft Windows and [[Dreamcast|Sega Dreamcast]] in 2000, and [[GameCube|Nintendo GameCube]] in 2003. Unlike the original, which uses [[tank controls]] and fixed camera angles, the remake features [[third-person shooter]] gameplay similar to the [[Resident Evil 2 (2019 video game)|2019 ''Resident Evil 2'' remake]]. {{anchor|Resident Evil: Resistance}}It includes an [[online multiplayer]] mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', which puts a team of four players against a \"mastermind\" who can create traps, enemies, and other hazards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wakeling |first1=Richard |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Official Release Date On Consoles And PC Announced; RE Resistance Multiplayer Included |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-official-release-date-on-co/1100-6472063/ |website=GameSpot |accessdate=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212111645/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-official-release-date-on-co/1100-6472063/ |archive-date=December 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The beginning of ''Resident Evil 3'' however, has players briefly controlling Jill in a [[first person perspective]], in a nightmare, and then in her apartment, engaging with the environment around her much like the characters the players assume the role of in ''[[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]''.<ref>https://www.gamerevolution.com/guides/641723-resident-evil-3-remake-first-person-mode-pc-ps4-xbox-one</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n[[Raccoon City]] is thrown into chaos by a [[zombie apocalypse]] caused by an outbreak of the [[T-Virus]]. On September 28, 1998, former Special Tactics And Rescue Service (S.T.A.R.S.) member [[Jill Valentine]] is attacked in her apartment by an intelligent [[Biological agent|bioweapon]] known as [[Nemesis (Resident Evil)|Nemesis-T Type]], who attempts to kill her and all remaining members of S.T.A.R.S.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shapiro |first1=Micah |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake: Clues For An Expanded Story |url=https://gamerant.com/resident-evil-3-remake-story-clues/ |website=Game Rant |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231255/https://gamerant.com/resident-evil-3-remake-story-clues/ |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Upon escaping her building, she meets up with fellow S.T.A.R.S. officer [[Brad Vickers]], but Brad is bitten by a zombie and tells Jill to save herself. After another encounter with Nemesis, she is saved by Umbrella Biohazard Countermeasure Service (U.B.C.S.) mercenary [[Carlos Oliveira (Resident Evil)|Carlos Oliveira]]. Carlos and his group of surviving U.B.C.S. mercenaries - [[Mikhail Victor]], Tyrell Patrick, and [[Nicholai Ginovaef]] - have set up subway trains which they plan to use to evacuate surviving civilians from the city. \n\nAfter surviving several encounters with Nemesis, Jill manages to reactivate power to the subway, while Carlos and Tyrell remain in the city to search for Dr. Nathaniel Bard, an Umbrella scientist who might know how to make a vaccine for the T-virus and save the city. As Jill, Nicholai, and Mikhail depart in the train, Mikhail expresses his suspicions towards Nicholai on how their platoon was ambushed by zombies. Nemesis suddenly attacks the train and kills the civilians; Nicholai locks the other two out, forcing them to defend themselves. Nemesis grabs Mikhail, who sacrifices himself by detonating an explosive, causing the train to derail. Jill escapes as seemingly the only survivor of the crash.\n\nCarlos and Tyrell travel to the city's police department, where they plan to find Bard in the S.T.A.R.S. office. The two witness R.P.D. Lieutenant Marvin Branagh be bitten by a zombified Brad, who is killed by Carlos shortly afterwards. The two enter the S.T.A.R.S. office and communicate via video with Bard, who informs them that he is at a hospital. Meanwhile, as Tyrell traces Bard\u2019s location, Jill escapes the wreckage of the derailed train only to be again pursued by Nemesis who is now heavily mutated. Jill radios Carlos and engages the monster, managing to escape it, but only after it infects her with the T-virus. Jill falls unconscious and Carlos finds her roughly half a day later, taking her to Spencer Memorial Hospital - the location of Bard. Carlos fights his way through the infested hospital only to find that Bard has been murdered. He views a video from Bard confessing that the T-virus was engineered by Umbrella, and despite Umbrella hiring him to develop the vaccine, Umbrella's board now wants to destroy it and eliminate all traces of the virus' existence. Carlos retrieves the vaccine and administers it to Jill. Tyrell arrives at the hospital and they realize that the U.S. government plans to destroy Raccoon City in a missile strike to eradicate the T-Virus infestation. Carlos travels to the NEST 2 lab underneath the hospital to find more vaccines, while Tyrell tries to contact whoever he can to try and stop the missile strike.\n\nJill awakens on the day of the missile strike, October 1, and pursues Carlos to NEST 2. She encounters Nicholai, who is revealed to be a supervisor hired by an unknown contractor to sabotage Umbrella's efforts to hide their involvement and to observe and collect data from attacks of several bioweapons, including Nemesis. Nemesis kills Tyrell and continues to pursue Jill throughout the lab. Jill manages to synthesize a vaccine, but an encounter with Nemesis causes Nicholai to retrieve it for himself as he leaves her to fight the monster. Jill attempts to destroy Nemesis in a vat of solution designed to dispose of any biological waste only for Nemesis to further mutate into a giant mass of flesh with tentacles. Jill then uses a prototype [[railgun]] to finally eliminate Nemesis for good. At the hospital's roof deck, Nicholai disarms Jill and destroys the vaccine, acknowledging that he doesn't care for the city's fate as long as he gets paid for sabotaging Umbrella. Carlos intervenes and restrains Nicholai for Jill to shoot.{{efn|If missed or not shot, Nicholai kills Jill and Carlos.<ref name=\"IGNdetails\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/21-brilliant-details-in-resident-evil-3|title=21 Brilliant Little Details in Resident Evil 3|website=IGN|date=3 April 2020|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>}} When interrogated on who he works for, he says that he will tell her and pay her anything if he survives. Disgusted by his greed, Jill retrieves the destroyed vaccine case and escapes the city with Carlos via helicopter, leaving Nicholai for dead. The city is destroyed by the missile strike, and Jill promises to take down Umbrella.\n\n==Development==\n''Resident Evil 3'' was under development for approximately three years prior to its announcement in 2019.<ref>{{cite web| last1=Palumbo |first1=Alessio |title='Resident Evil 3' Has Far More Raccoon City Exploration Dodge Makes It Feel More Like an Action Game |url=https://wccftech.com/resident-evil-3-has-far-more-raccoon-city-exploration-dodge-makes-it-feel-more-like-an-action-game/ |website=wccftech |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307094447/https://wccftech.com/resident-evil-3-has-far-more-raccoon-city-exploration-dodge-makes-it-feel-more-like-an-action-game/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Possible remake\">{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/capcom-says-a-resident-evil-3-remake-is-possible-i-say-bring-it-on--541068.phtml |title=Capcom says a Resident Evil 3 remake is possible, I say 'bring it on' |website=[[Destructoid]] |last=Carter |first=Chris |date=February 2, 2019 |accessdate=February 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203082435/https://www.destructoid.com/capcom-says-a-resident-evil-3-remake-is-possible-i-say-bring-it-on--541068.phtml |archivedate=February 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Fabiano speaks with GamingBolt\">{{cite web| last1=Parijat |first1= Shubhankar |title=Resident Evil 3 Interview \u2013 Return to Raccoon City | url=https://gamingbolt.com/resident-evil-3-interview-return-to-raccoon-city |website=gamingbolt |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324211016/https://gamingbolt.com/resident-evil-3-interview-return-to-raccoon-city |archive-date=March 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Development was handled by [[Capcom]] with assistance from its subsidiary K2 Inc, and from external companies Redworks and M-Two, the latter being founded by former [[PlatinumGames]] CEO Tatsuya Minami.<ref name=\"Director\">{{cite web|last1=Robinson |first1=Andy |title=Platinum veteran revealed as Resident Evil 3 director |url=https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/platinum-veteran-revealed-as-resident-evil-3-director/ |website=videogameschronicle |accessdate=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310004438/https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/platinum-veteran-revealed-as-resident-evil-3-director/ |archive-date=March 10, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://k2-games.com/|title=K2 Inc Official Page|accessdate=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324210022/http://k2-games.com/|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Minami's M-Two\">{{cite web|last1=Robinson |first1=Andy |title=Confirmed Former Platinum CEO is behind new Capcom-backed studio |url=https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/confirmed-former-platinum-ceo-is-behind-new-capcom-backed-studio/ |website=videogameschronicle |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330232332/https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/confirmed-former-platinum-ceo-is-behind-new-capcom-backed-studio/ |archive-date=March 31, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The game was created using the RE Engine that was used in ''[[Resident Evil 7]]'', ''[[Devil May Cry 5]]'' and the ''Resident Evil 2'' remake.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Holt |first1=Kris |title='Resident Evil 3' remake hits PS4, Xbox One and PC on April 3rd |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-release-date/ |website=Engadget |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210213744/https://www.engadget.com/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-release-date/ |archive-date=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The multiplayer mode, ''Resident Evil: Resistance'', was developed externally by NeoBards Entertainment and was previously announced as a separate game, ''Project Resistance''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/350590/Capcom_Unveils_Project_Resistance_a_New_Experience_Set_in_the_Resident_Evil_Universe.php|title=Capcom Unveils Project Resistance; a New Experience Set in the Resident Evil Universe|website=Gamasutra|accessdate=12 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211231407/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/350590/Capcom_Unveils_Project_Resistance_a_New_Experience_Set_in_the_Resident_Evil_Universe.php|archive-date=December 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProducers Masachika Kawata and Peter Fabiano said the team tried to honor the more action-oriented approach of the original game.<ref name=\"DevMsg\">{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Alistair |title=The Resident Evil 3 Remake is Real, and it Comes with Project Resistance |url=https://www.kotaku.co.uk/2019/12/10/the-resident-evil-3-remake-is-real-and-it-comes-with-project-resistance |website=Kotaku |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211214352/https://www.kotaku.co.uk/2019/12/10/the-resident-evil-3-remake-is-real-and-it-comes-with-project-resistance |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> They altered character designs accordingly, with Jill wearing more practical apparel and Carlos Oliveira being \"more rough around the edges\".<ref name=\"DevMsg\"/> Nemesis, one of the central aspects of the game, was redesigned and given new ways to track down players compared to the Tyrant from ''Resident Evil 2''.<ref name=\"DevMsg\"/> In terms of its visual design, Fabiano mentioned that art director Yonghee Cho wanted to make Nemesis feel like he could fit in the reimagined and photorealistic Raccoon City and should feel like a prototype model, while adding that the development team wanted to give players the feeling that they were constantly being pursued by a relentless and agile bioweapon by striking a balance between having players feel anxious and also giving them periods of respite.<ref name=\"Fabiano speaks with GamingBolt\"/>\n\n==Release==\n''Resident Evil 3'' was announced during an online PlayStation presentation in December 2019, and was released on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\"Remake confirmed\">{{cite web |first=Chris|last=Priestman|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-confirmed-with-release-date |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Confirmed With Release Date |website=[[IGN]] |date=December 10, 2019 |accessdate=December 10, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210215425/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/12/10/resident-evil-3-remake-confirmed-with-release-date |archivedate=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> A collector's edition was made available for the console versions and features a Jill Valentine figure, hardcover art book, Raccoon City map poster, and two-disc soundtrack.<ref name=\"Collectors edition\">{{cite web |first=Jenae |last=Sitzes |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-pre-order-guide-collectors-/1100-6472065/ |title=Resident Evil 3 Remake Pre-Order Guide: Collector's Edition, Release Date, Pre-Order Bonus |website=[[GameSpot]] |date=December 11, 2019 |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211214238/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-3-remake-pre-order-guide-collectors-/1100-6472065/ |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Romano |first1=Sal |title=Resident Evil 3 remake Collector\u2019s Edition announced for Europe |url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/resident-evil-3-remake-collectors-edition-announced-for-europe |website=Gematsu |accessdate=January 22, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125100943/https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/resident-evil-3-remake-collectors-edition-announced-for-europe |archive-date=January 25, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> A demo of the game was released on March 19, 2020, with a ''Resident Evil: Resistance'' beta released on March 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/resident-evil-3-demo-to-be-released-on-march-19-resident-evil-resistance-arriving-on-march-27|title=Resident Evil 3 Demo to be Released on March 19, Resident Evil Resistance Open Beta Arriving on March 27|first=Adam|last=Bankhurst|website=[[IGN]]|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (PC) 78/100<ref name=\"MCPC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/resident-evil-3 |title=Resident Evil 3 for PC Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref><br/>(PS4) 80/100<ref name=\"MCPS4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/resident-evil-3|title=Resident Evil 3 for PlayStation 4 Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><br/>(XONE) 84/100<ref name=\"MCXONE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/resident-evil-3|title=Resident Evil